---
---

<section class="section research">
  <div class="container research-grid">
    <div class="research-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">Grounded in research</p>
      <h2 class="h1">Every claim cites the study behind it.</h2>
      <p class="subhead">
        AI is easy. Honest AI is harder.
      </p>
      <p class="research-body">
        Meld's coach is trained to ground its advice in published research,
        not in vibes. When Meld says <em>"your deep sleep improves when you eat more protein at lunch,"</em> it links the actual paper that shows why.
      </p>
      <p class="research-body">
        You can click the citation. Read the study. Trust your own judgment.
      </p>
    </div>

    <aside class="citation-card" aria-hidden="true">
      <div class="cite-header">
        <span class="cite-tag">Paired insight</span>
        <span class="cite-conn">Protein <span class="arrow">→</span> Deep sleep</span>
      </div>
      <p class="cite-finding">
        Your deep sleep averaged <strong>18% higher</strong> this week on days
        you ate &gt;110g protein by 2pm.
      </p>
      <div class="cite-source">
        <svg
          width="18"
          height="18"
          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
          fill="none"
          stroke="currentColor"
          stroke-width="1.5"
          stroke-linecap="round"
          stroke-linejoin="round"
        >
          <path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z" />
          <polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8" />
          <line x1="8" y1="13" x2="16" y2="13" />
          <line x1="8" y1="17" x2="16" y2="17" />
        </svg>
        <span>
          Peuhkuri K, et al. <em>Diet promotes sleep duration and quality.</em>
          Nutrition Research (2012)
        </span>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .research {
    background: var(--bg-primary);
  }

  .research-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--sp-12);
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    align-items: center;
  }

  @media (min-width: 900px) {
    .research-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1.15fr 1fr;
      gap: var(--sp-16);
    }
  }

  .research-copy {
    max-width: 52ch;
  }

  .research-copy .h1 {
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-5);
  }

  .research-copy .subhead {
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-5);
  }

  .research-body {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-weight: var(--fw-light);
    line-height: var(--lh-relaxed);
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);
  }

  .research-body em {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .citation-card {
    background: var(--purple-100);
    border-radius: var(--r-card-lg);
    padding: var(--sp-6);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-card);
    max-width: 440px;
    width: 100%;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .cite-header {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--sp-2);
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);
  }

  .cite-tag {
    font-size: var(--fs-label);
    font-weight: var(--fw-medium);
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--purple-600);
  }

  .cite-conn {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: var(--fw-regular);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .arrow {
    color: var(--purple-500);
    font-weight: var(--fw-light);
    margin-inline: 4px;
  }

  .cite-finding {
    font-size: var(--fs-body);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--lh-relaxed);
    padding-bottom: var(--sp-4);
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(84, 56, 166, 0.12);
  }

  .cite-finding strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-weight: var(--fw-medium);
  }

  .cite-source {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--sp-2);
    font-size: var(--fs-caption);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--lh-snug);
  }

  .cite-source svg {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    color: var(--purple-500);
  }

  .cite-source em {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-style: italic;
  }
</style>
